{
  "id": "ACT.24",
  "bibleId": "de4e12af7f28f599-01",
  "number": "24",
  "bookId": "ACT",
  "reference": "Acts 24",
  "copyright": "PUBLIC DOMAIN except in the United Kingdom, where a Crown Copyright applies to printing the KJV. See http://www.cambridge.org/about-us/who-we-are/queens-printers-patent",
  "verseCount": 27,
  "content": [
    {
      "name": "para",
      "type": "tag",
      "attrs": {
        "style": "p"
      },
      "items": [
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "1",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:1"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "1",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And after five days Ananias the high priest descended with the elders, and ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.1",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.1"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "with",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.1",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.1"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " a certain orator ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.1",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.1"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "named",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.1",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.1"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " Tertullus, who informed the governor against Paul. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.1",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.1"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "2",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:2"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "2",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And when he was called forth, Tertullus began to accuse ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.2",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.2"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "him",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.2",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.2"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ", saying, Seeing that by thee we enjoy great quietness, and that very worthy deeds are done unto this nation by thy providence, ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.2",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.2"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "3",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:3"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "3",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "We accept ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.3",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.3"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "it",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.3",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.3"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " always, and in all places, most noble Felix, with all thankfulness. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.3",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.3"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "4",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:4"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "4",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Notwithstanding, that I be not further tedious unto thee, I pray thee that thou wouldest hear us of thy clemency a few words. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.4",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.4"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "5",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:5"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "5",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For we have found this man ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.5",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.5"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "a",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.5",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.5"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " pestilent ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.5",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.5"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "fellow",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.5",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.5"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ", and a mover of sedition among all the Jews throughout the world, and a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes: ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.5",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.5"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "6",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:6"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "6",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Who also hath gone about to profane the temple: whom we took, and would have judged according to our law. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.6",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.6"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "7",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:7"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "7",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But the chief captain Lysias came ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.7",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.7"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "upon us",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.7",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.7"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ", and with great violence took ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.7",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.7"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "him",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.7",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.7"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " away out of our hands, ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.7",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.7"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "8",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:8"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "8",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Commanding his accusers to come unto thee: by examining of whom thyself mayest take knowledge of all these things, whereof we accuse him. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.8",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.8"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "9",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:9"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "9",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And the Jews also assented, saying that these things were so. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.9",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.9"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "10",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:10"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "10",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Then Paul, after that the governor had beckoned unto him to speak, answered, Forasmuch as I know that thou hast been of many years a judge unto this nation, I do the more cheerfully answer for myself: ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.10",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.10"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "11",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:11"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "11",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Because that thou mayest understand, that there are yet but twelve days since I went up to Jerusalem for to worship. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.11",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.11"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "12",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:12"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "12",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And they neither found me in the temple disputing with any man, neither raising up the people, neither in the synagogues, nor in the city: ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.12",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.12"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "13",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:13"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "13",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Neither can they prove the things whereof they now accuse me. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.13",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.13"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "14",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:14"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "14",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But this I confess unto thee, that after the way which they call heresy, so worship I the God of my fathers, believing all things which are written in the law and in the prophets: ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.14",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.14"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "15",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:15"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "15",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And have hope toward God, which they themselves also allow, that there shall be a resurrection of the dead, both of the just and unjust. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.15",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.15"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "16",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:16"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "16",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And herein do I exercise myself, to have always a conscience void of offence toward God, and ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.16",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.16"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "toward",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.16",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.16"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " men. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.16",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.16"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "17",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:17"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "17",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Now after many years I came to bring alms to my nation, and offerings. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.17",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.17"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "18",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:18"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "18",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Whereupon certain Jews from Asia found me purified in the temple, neither with multitude, nor with tumult. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.18",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.18"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "19",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:19"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "19",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Who ought to have been here before thee, and object, if they had ought against me. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.19",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.19"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "20",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:20"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "20",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Or else let these same ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.20",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.20"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "here",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.20",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.20"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " say, if they have found any evil doing in me, while I stood before the council, ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.20",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.20"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "21",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:21"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "21",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Except it be for this one voice, that I cried standing among them, Touching the resurrection of the dead I am called in question by you this day.",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.21",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.21"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "para",
      "type": "tag",
      "attrs": {
        "style": "p"
      },
      "items": [
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "22",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:22"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "22",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And when Felix heard these things, having more perfect knowledge of ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.22",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.22"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "that",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.22",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.22"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " way, he deferred them, and said, When Lysias the chief captain shall come down, I will know the uttermost of your matter. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.22",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.22"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "23",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:23"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "23",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And he commanded a centurion to keep Paul, and to let ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.23",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.23"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "him",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "ACT.24.23",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "ACT.24.23"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " have liberty, and that he should forbid none of his acquaintance to minister or come unto him.",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.23",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.23"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "para",
      "type": "tag",
      "attrs": {
        "style": "p"
      },
      "items": [
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "24",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:24"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "24",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And after certain days, when Felix came with his wife Drusilla, which was a Jewess, he sent for Paul, and heard him concerning the faith in Christ. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.24",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.24"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "25",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:25"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "25",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And as he reasoned of righteousness, temperance, and judgment to come, Felix trembled, and answered, Go thy way for this time; when I have a convenient season, I will call for thee. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.25",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.25"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "26",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:26"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "26",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "He hoped also that money should have been given him of Paul, that he might loose him: wherefore he sent for him the oftener, and communed with him. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "ACT.24.26",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "ACT.24.26"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "27",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "ACT 24:27"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "27",
